::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_2000254_462-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_2000254_462-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Go on.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200025406-->
:::'''Esther:''' Once, in the Department of Galactic Geopolitics, there were two well-known young people. They were not only comrades in arms with similar interests but also a couple who pushed each other to become better.
:::'''Esther:''' They were committed to fighting for the weak and upholding justice for those who were trampled by Aeons and their factions.
:::'''Esther:''' Until one day, justice was no longer just an ideal. A Lord Ravager came to the female researcher's hometown, and her home planet was about to be destroyed. For the first time ever, the two disagreed on how justice should be implemented in this scenario.
:::'''Esther:''' The female researcher chose to return to her home planet alone to alert them of the disaster, but unexpectedly, an accident occurred during her journey.
:::'''Esther:''' At the time, the star rail was blocked by a Stellaron and her spacecraft was also stranded in the path of the Antimatter Legion. In absolute fear, she chose to call the Herta Space Station for help.
:::'''Esther:''' However, the space station had chosen to remain neutral in all actions involving the Aeons, and the operator responsible for relaying this ruthless message was none other than the male researcher himself.
:::'''Esther:''' Through the radio, he personally witnessed how his stranded lover ran out of oxygen in the damaged aircraft and how she slowly died drifting into the endless darkness.
:::'''Esther:''' ... For some reason, this tragic story just came to mind today. Thought I'd share it with you.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_2000254_472-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_2000254_472-->
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The researcher in the story is...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200025415-->
::::'''Esther:''' Ha, that's not important. I'm just telling a story. Any resemblance to real-life events is purely coincidental.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} She gave her life for "justice."
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200025417-->
::::'''Esther:''' Yes, she was a real hero.
::::'''Esther:''' After her death, the researchers reexamined the question of justice. If we spend our whole life debating justice but choose to stand idly by when there are actual injustices happening all over the cosmos, then what we're really doing is just making a mockery of justice.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} This must have been tormenting for him.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200025420-->
::::'''Esther:''' Maybe. However, I believe that in his long life, he must have found a way to make up for the past and obtain peace.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_200025421-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200025421-->
:::'''Esther:''' Well, that's all for today. Please take these rewards. I hope to see you again in the future.
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I have other matters to attend to...
